cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper deals with image super-resolution, which is a subfield of computer vision. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper focuses on improving the quality of compressed images, which is a common problem in multimedia applications. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes an end-to-end trainable deep convolutional neural network for image super-resolution, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper discusses the application of the proposed method in low bit-rate image coding, which is relevant to information retrieval. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper explores the rate-distortion performance of the proposed method, which is a topic of interest in information theory.
